## Why `brandContext` is still null

Partner Repository currently returns no brand/entity field in `UserResponse`. Your logs show user details including name, email, phone, language, and status, but no `entity`.

You need to add it through the full chain:

```text
UserEntity.entity
  -> UserInfoResponse or UserResponse.entity
  -> Arthur Core Partner Repository DTO
  -> UserSession.brandContext
  -> HandoffExchangeResponse.brandContext
```

The simplest structure is to add it directly to `UserResponse`:

```java
private String entity;
```

Then map:

```java
response.setEntity(user.getEntity());
```

In Arthur:

```java
session.setBrandContext(userResponse.getEntity());
```

Then during handoff:

```java
response.setBrandContext(session.getBrandContext());
```

After this, the Stub Server should log something like:

```text
email=john.doe@orange.example.com
firstName=John
lastName=Doe
brandContext=ORANGE
```

